Orange (GUI) is an open-source data visualization, machine learning, and data mining toolkit that provides an intuitive, easy-to-use graphical user interface (GUI). It allows users to create data analysis workflows through a visual programming environment by connecting widgets that represent different data processing, visualization, and modeling tasks. Orange is commonly used for:

- Data analysis
- Data visualization
- Machine learning
- Exploratory data analysis

Key features include:

- Interactive workflows for data preprocessing, feature scoring, and visualization.
- Integration of various machine learning algorithms and techniques.
- Extensive support for add-ons, such as bioinformatics or text mining.

